Combine rows of named list of 2-column data.frames

Source: R/helpers.R
make_df_from_named_list.Rd

This function is an internal, helper function used by ana_fn functions to combine p-values across several variables.

make_df_from_named_list(
  list,
  index = "Var",
  value = paste0("Value", 1:length(list[[1]]))
)

Arguments

list

Named list of data.frames

index

Variable name to store data.frame names

value

Variable name for value stored in each data.frame (in ana_fn functions, typically a p-value)

Value

data.frame with combined rows and 2 columns

See also

ana_fn_aov(), ana_fn_rm_aov(), ana_fn_chisq()
